Whereas previous work (Yarowsky, 1992; Gale, et aal., 1992, 1993) relies heavily on the role of statistics, the present system makes use of Machine Readable/Tractable Dictionaries (Wilks, et aal., 1990; Guo, in press) and an example-based reasoning technique (Nagao, 1984; Sumita, et aal., 1990) to treat novel words, compound words, and phrases found in the input text.
